[[File:Great Generals of the Desert and the Spirits of Grasses and Trees Who Dwell in the Void of Water and Land.jpg|thumb|''Great Generals of the Desert and the Spirits of Grasses and Trees Who Dwell in the Void of Water and Land'', part of the Water and Land Ritual paintings]] The '''Water and Land Ritual paintings''' is a set thirty six [[Chinese mythology|Chinese mythological]] paintings from 1454.<ref name="chinese">{{cite book | authors=Marsha Smith Weidner, Patricia Ann Berger, Helen Foresman Spencer Museum of Art, Asian Art Museum of San Francisco| title =Latter Days of the Law: Images of Chinese Buddhism, 850 - 1850| publisher =University of Hawaii Press| year =1994| page =286| isbn =0824816625}}</ref> The paintings were part of a larger set, as indicated by the incomplete representation of certain themes on the extant scrolls.<ref name="chinese"/> The majority of paintings (thirty four) are housed in the [[Guimet Museum]] and the remaining two are kept in the [[Cleveland Museum of Art]].
